      critical_gap: 'Dismisses the pledge risk because "the underlying business is fundamentally sound." The business may be sound but the stock price is governed by the forced sale dynamics, not fundamentals. Fails to calculate the market\'s ability to absorb ₹1,779 Cr of forced selling against ₹12 Cr daily volume.',
      non_obvious_signal: 'The stock is only 7% above the margin call trigger (₹298 vs ₹320 CMP). This means ANY negative catalyst — even unrelated to the company — could trigger the cascade. The risk is not about fundamentals; it\'s about market microstructure. A fundamentally sound company can lose 40-50% of market cap purely because of promoter pledge mechanics. The business DCF is irrelevant until the pledge overhang is resolved.',
