    market_context: 'Indian generic pharma companies dependent on US formulations face structural headwinds: (1) US FDA price erosion for generics has accelerated to 15-20% annually for commoditised molecules, (2) ANDA (drug approval) pipeline depletion — new approvals are taking longer and targeting smaller markets, (3) biosimilars require 3-5x the investment of traditional generics.\n\nThe "cheap vs peers" argument ignores why the stock is cheap. The pharma sector P/E of 28x applies to companies with growing US pipelines and stable margins. AuroMed\'s US margins are compressing at 600bps/year, and its ANDA pipeline is depleting without adequate R&D reinvestment.',
